                          Hi Steven!

The following program, life, generates fancy patterns on your screen.
Each 'generation' is calculated from the previous one; a grid cell is
considered alive if it has either 3 or 4 direct neighbours in the
previous generation, dead if it has not.
The program must be run in either high or medium resolution.
The source file has been submitted to the sources group.

